# JavaScript DOM – Manipulation

---

## 📘 Changing Content

### textContent vs innerHTML vs innerText

```js
const el = document.querySelector("p");

// textContent — raw text (no HTML parsing, safe)
el.textContent = "Hello World";
el.textContent;  // "Hello World"

// innerHTML — parses HTML tags (⚠️ XSS risk with user input)
el.innerHTML = "<strong>Hello</strong> World";
el.innerHTML;  // "<strong>Hello</strong> World"

// innerText — visible text only (respects CSS, slower)
el.innerText = "Hello";
```

> **Security rule:** Never use `innerHTML` with user-supplied data. Use `textContent` for plain text.

