## 🎨 Changing Styles

### Inline Styles (style property)
```js
const box = document.querySelector(".box");

box.style.color = "red";
box.style.backgroundColor = "blue";    // camelCase for CSS properties
box.style.fontSize = "20px";
box.style.display = "none";
box.style.cssText = "color:red; font-size:20px;"; // set multiple
```

### CSS Classes (best practice)
```js
const el = document.querySelector(".card");

el.classList.add("active");           // add a class
el.classList.remove("hidden");        // remove a class
el.classList.toggle("dark");          // add if absent, remove if present
el.classList.contains("active");      // true / false
el.classList.replace("old", "new");   // replace one class

// className (sets/gets entire class string)
el.className = "card active featured"; // replaces ALL classes
```

