## 🏷️ Working with Attributes

```js
const img = document.querySelector("img");

// Get
img.getAttribute("src")       // "photo.jpg"
img.getAttribute("alt")       // "Photo"

// Set
img.setAttribute("src", "new.jpg");
img.setAttribute("alt", "New Photo");

// Remove
img.removeAttribute("alt");

// Check
img.hasAttribute("src")       // true

// Direct property access (for standard HTML attributes)
img.src           // full URL
img.alt           // "Photo"
img.id
img.href          // on <a> tags
img.value         // on <input> tags
img.checked       // on checkboxes

// data-* attributes
// HTML: <div data-user-id="42" data-role="admin">
el.dataset.userId   // "42"   (camelCase mapping)
el.dataset.role     // "admin"
el.dataset.userId = "99";  // set
```

